Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules
info.description:
ParseTime is a simple Python extension module that simply wraps the parsetime()
function that is used internally by the familiar "at" Unix command.  This allows
a programmer to parse a complicated expression that represents a particular
point in time.
info.name: ParseTime
info.summary: Contains a function that parses complicated time expressions.
